<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-10T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/12–1049: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-10T18:00:00+01:00">December
                                    10, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:19 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4041. ReEmbtel 3991, December 7. Informed [that] Foreign Office has
                            replied to British memorandum that, while they agree with British
                            reasoning, they consider unity among Western democracies on issue of
                            recognition more important. We have been promised text of reply and
                            shall forward it as soon as received.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dunn</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>